# Normalize all text to LF in the repo on every platform. Linux is the
# primary host and the .sh experiment drivers / tool scripts must stay LF
# to execute; Windows is a secondary dev machine where editors otherwise
# write CRLF. Enforcing eol=lf repo-wide keeps line endings off every diff
# regardless of which machine committed. The whole repo is already LF, so
# this introduces no renormalization — it locks in current state and makes
# it independent of any per-machine core.autocrlf setting.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets git must never line-ending-convert (data, model weights,
# montages, compiled libs, recordings, archives).
*.fif binary
*.npz binary
*.npy binary
*.pt binary
*.pth binary
*.onnx binary
*.so binary
*.xdf binary
*.pkl binary
*.h5 binary
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.pdf binary
*.zip binary
